{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, tasks such as semantic and instance segmentation require greater attention to detail, significantly increasing the labelling time per example.Self-supervised learning (SSL) has emerged as a broad strategy to learn a machine learning model that produces feature representations from unlabelled data.",
    "It is particularly beneficial when only a subset of examples in a dataset have associated labels.",
    "In brief, a machine learning model (typically a deep neural network) is trained to optimize a supervised learning objective in which the targets can be derived from the inputs themselves.",
    "In other words, a model is trained to solve a pretext task, which is a problem that is solvable using only the inputs and that requires no labels.",
    "Self-supervised pretraining refers to the optimization of a self-supervised objective to obtain a model capable of producing meaningful feature representations that capture salient information available in the inputs."
  ]
}